records.addlTxt:
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) AODA assessment and follow through;
2) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
4) Pay court costs, including $367.31 buy money to Metro Drug Unit:
5) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
6) spend six (6) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, commencing on 07-21-15 by 5:00 p.m.  Court also allows release for child care purposes;
7) take all medications as prescribed, in prescribed doses and use only one doctor and one pharmacist;
8) maintain fulltime employment if physically able to do so  at the agents discretion;
9) spend an additional three (3) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, stayed and to be imposed at the agents discretion and upon order of the court.
The Court will entertain a motion for early discharge if recommended by the agent.
Minutes.
